When editing `vercel.json`:

- Ensure the following settings:
  ```json
  {
    "builds": [
      {
        "src": "next.config.js",
        "use": "@vercel/next"
      }
    ],
    "routes": [
      { "src": "/api/(.*)", "dest": "https://leadpulse-backend.onrender.com/$1" },
      { "src": "/(.*)", "dest": "/$1" }
    ]
  }
  ```
Proxy API requests to the Render backend (leadpulse-backend.onrender.com).
Test configuration locally with vercel dev.
Deploy a preview URL (vercel) to verify routing.
Add environment variables via vercel env add (e.g., NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL).
Reference environment variables in next.config.js:
```javascript
module.exports = {
  env: {
    NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL,
  },
};
```
